Refilwe Mtsweni-Tsipane said she regrets the incident and had made a statement of guilt at Vosman Police Station in Emalahleni. She also accepted the necessary fine. Mtsweni-Tsipane was seen walking some distance and hugging officials without wearing a face mask at the funeral of Minister in the Presidency, Jackson Mthembu. She has apologised to the family of Mthembu, President Cyril Ramaphosa and the people of Mpumalanga. Wearing of a mask in public was made mandatory under Level 3 lockdown regulations. South Africa is the country worst-hit by the pandemic in Africa. --BBC--